contributor: WNUR (Radio station : Evanston, Ill.)|Gregory, Dick|Kastenmeier, Robert|McCarthy, Eugene J., 1916-2005|Lucey, Patrick J., 1918-2014|Wallace, George C. (George Corley), 1919-1998
creator: Northwestern University (Evanston, Ill.)
description: Recordings from WNUR involving the 1968 Presidential Election. Part 1 is from a series of speeches at the University of Wisconsin. Then governor Patrick Lucey introduces Robert Kastenmeier and Gene McCarthy. Kastenmeier and McCarthy discuss the 1968 Presidential election, the 1968 Democratic convention in Chicago, violence in society, and the Vietnam War. Recorded on 10/20/68. Part 2 - George C. Wallace speaks at Monument Square in downtown Oshkosh, Wisconsin. He discusses his platform as a candidate for president in the 1968 Presidental Election. Recorded on 10/22/68 ; Part 3 - Dick Gregory speaks at the Great Hall of the University of Wisconsin. Gregory discusses his platform as a write-in candidate during the 1968 Presidential Election. Recorded on 10/22/68. Part 4 - News update
